│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The loop-vectorizer crashes with an assertion in                              │
│ VPTransformState::get(VPValue*, bool) that fires when a client requests a     │
│ single scalar per part (NeedsScalar=true) for a VPValue that already has      │
│ multiple per-lane scalar values cached. The specific assertion verifies that  │
│ when onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) is true, there must be exactly one scalar         │
│ recorded (the first lane) for that Def. The reproducer constructs a           │
│ predicated instruction feeding a phi/select (VPBlend) whose users only        │
│ consume the first lane, but the VPlan execution generates scalars for all     │
│ lanes for the VPPredInstPHIRecipe, violating the assertion.                   │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - The debug-only=vplan trace shows a replicated, predicated udiv, with        │
│ VPPredInstPHIRecipes merging values inside predicated regions:                │
│ pred.udiv.if/pred.udiv.continue blocks. Later, during VPBlendRecipe::execute, │
│ it queries inputs using State.get(..., OnlyFirstLaneUsed) where               │
│ OnlyFirstLaneUsed = vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) on the VPBlend.          │
│ - The crash happens in VPTransformState::get when NeedsScalar=true for a Def  │
│ that is a VPPredInstPHIRecipe (from debugger:                                 │
│ Def->getDefiningRecipe()->getVPDefID() = 26, which maps to                    │
│ VPPredInstPHIRecipe).                                                         │
│ - The assertion condition includes !vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def) ||        │
│ (hasScalarValue(Def, lane0) && Data.VPV2Scalars[Def].size() == 1). We         │
│ violated this because onlyFirstLaneUsed(Def)==true but multiple lanes were    │
│ populated for Def.                                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ - VPPredInstPHIRecipe::execute is executed in a replicator region with        │
│ State.Lane set for each lane. It unconditionally creates and caches a scalar  │
│ phi for the current lane (State.set(this, Phi, *State.Lane)) when its operand │
│ has no vector value. This happens for all lanes 0..VF-1. Later, a user        │
│ (VPBlend) determines only first lane is needed                                │
│ (vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) == true) and calls State.get(...,           │
│ NeedsScalar=true). This requires that the producer’s value be available as a  │
│ single scalar (first lane only). However, because VPPredInstPHIRecipe already │
│ produced scalars for multiple lanes, the assertion fires.                     │
│ - Other recipes that can produce per-lane values already honor                │
│ onlyFirstLaneUsed and limit generation to the first lane (see                 │
│ VPScalarIVStepsRecipe::execute and VPInstruction::generate paths).            │
│ VPPredInstPHIRecipe::execute was missing this guard.                          │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                     │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlanRecipes.cpp, function              │
│ VPPredInstPHIRecipe::execute.                                                 │
│ - Add a guard to honor vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) and skip generating   │
│ per-lane phis for lanes > 0. This ensures that if all users only use the      │
│ first lane, the recipe records exactly one scalar (lane 0), satisfying the    │
│ assertion in VPTransformState::get.                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Suggested patch (conceptual):                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ void VPPredInstPHIRecipe::execute(VPTransformState &State) {                  │
│   assert(State.Lane && "Predicated instruction PHI works per instance.");     │
│   // If only the first lane is used by all users, avoid generating per-lane   │
│   // scalars for lanes > 0. This keeps a single scalar per part, as required  │
│   // by VPTransformState::get when NeedsScalar=true.                          │
│   if (vputils::onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) && !State.Lane->isFirstLane())         │
│     return;                                                                   │
│   ... existing code ...                                                       │
│ }                                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ - This change mirrors the approach used in other recipes to restrict codegen  │
│ based on onlyFirstLaneUsed.                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The crash is caused by VPPredInstPHIRecipe unconditionally generating         │
│ per-lane scalars even when downstream users demand only the first lane.       │
│ Adding a guard to skip lane>0 generation when onlyFirstLaneUsed(this) is true │
│ keeps the producer consistent with consumers’ expectations and satisfies      │
│ VPTransformState::get()’s assertion, fixing the abort in the provided         │
│ reproducer.                                                                   │
